(51, 2, '2013-10-04 10:57:10', '2013-10-04 10:57:10', 'Ok, here we go.\n\nI originally had quite an ugly name for the project, so decided to rename it. I was trying to figure out a name which would be catchy and relate to the essence of P2P networks. I also wanted to distance Nebel.TV from the current trend of “cloud based” solutions. Still the cloud is widely known and is a good metaphor for IT centralization as the virtuality of a cloud (<i>though I’d question its persistence and control!</i>).\n\nSo I asked myself: “What is the closest term to ‘cloud’ but doesn’t have its ‘singularity’ or ‘objectivism’?” And here’s what I arrived at: a <b>MIST (fog)</b>.\n\nA couple of minutes later I got the domain name but realized there are so many similar sounding projects and brands out there on the market. Which is never good, in respect to originality?\n\nThe friend of mine also pointed out that MIST doesn’t sound good in German.  :)\n\nSo, what other variants did I have instead of using the German’s ‘mist’: <b>NEBEL </b>[''ni:bəl]? Apparently it has got no bad meaning in other common languages (correct me if I wrong!).\n\nSo that’s it, a short but funny story.', 'Why it is "nebel"? ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'why-it-is-nebel', '', '', '2013-10-04 10:57:10', '2013-10-04 10:57:10', '', 0, 'http://www.nebel.tv/?p=51', 0, 'post', '', 0),
