(93, 2, '2013-10-16 12:51:25', '2013-10-16 12:51:25', 'I’ve just returned from an interesting event.\n\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1407938666102074/">https://www.facebook.com/events/1407938666102074/</a>\n\nOrganised by a team aiming to make a kind of “Social TV” internet service in Ukraine. The idea is based around community sourcing, founding and cooperation. Although I think this is a great idea, I can’t quite see a way they can profit from their service. Their financial prediction is to break-even having around 120,000 premium subscribers. Although the subscription fee is low, it is unlikely to be successful taking into account their current content.\n\nWould Nebel.TV help them? Hmm…Certainly to the extent of audience reach or integrated payments. Other than that: unlikely.\n\nStill it’s very interesting that people approach the TV revitalization not only from a technological concept but also from content and social perspectives. Here we’re undoubtedly in the same boat.\n\nGood luck to all of us!', 'Spilno.TV', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'spilno-tv', '', '', '2013-10-16 12:51:25', '2013-10-16 12:51:25', '', 0, 'http://www.nebel.tv/?p=59', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(94, 2, '2013-10-17 19:42:55', '2013-10-17 19:42:55', 'Today was my first full work day as a freelancer. I must admit that it has been one of the most inspiring days in the last few years. I was full of ideas, willing to work and found great people to help me.\n\nInteresting that Kiev has become saturated with co-working places. This is my current selection: http://startupukraine.com/kyivworking/\n\nSo here is my office:\n<a href="http://www.nebel.tv/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/image.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-65" alt="Office" src="http://www.nebel.tv/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/image-1024x318.jpg" width="604" height="187" /></a>\n\nAnd here is my boss:\n<a href="http://www.nebel.tv/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/image1.jpg"><img class="alignright size-large wp-image-66" alt="The Boss" src="http://www.nebel.tv/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/image1-1024x768.jpg" width="604" height="453" /></a>', 'Freelancing world welcomes me!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'freelancing-world-welcomes-me', '', '', '2013-10-17 19:42:55', '2013-10-17 19:42:55', '', 0, 'http://www.nebel.tv/?p=64', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(95, 2, '2013-10-23 10:00:19', '2013-10-23 10:00:19', 'The Nebel.TV team is finanally here. People added with no particular order. :)\n\n[slideshow_deploy id=''89'']\n\nYou can flip on people and pause the slideshow by mouse hovers over the picture.', 'The Nebel Team', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', 'theteam4nebel', 'the-nebel-team', '', '', '2013-10-23 10:00:19', '2013-10-23 10:00:19', '', 0, 'http://www.nebel.tv/?p=69', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(106, 2, '2013-11-13 07:01:08', '2013-11-13 07:01:08', 'One of the most difficult things in open projects is sharing. Although it isn''t the right time now to keep people updated (especially there are only a dozen or so people who are currently interested :)\n\nStill, the habit needs to be developed. So here are a few updates:\n<ul>\n	<li>Our primary activity as of now is the website, which we hope to lunch in the course of a couple of weeks; we''ve got an incredible design from Andrew - full of animation and JavaScript - but that''s quite difficult and time-consuming to implement. Luckily for us, there are many smart people around who are helping us make it happen.</li>\n	<li>The day before yesterday was a big day for the project. The first piece of Android code was released!! That was the TeaserApp - Sprint 1. No, I don''t want to share that just yet, as you''ll probably find that it looks nothing like Nebel.TV, but trust me it usually works like that!</li>\n	<li>Now there are 16(!) people on team Nebel.TV varying in skills from PR&amp;Media to in-depth development expertise; In later posts I will explain what we all do, why and what our intended output.</li>\n</ul>\nStay tuned! :)', 'Updates', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'updates', '', '', '2013-11-13 07:01:08', '2013-11-13 07:01:08', '', 0, 'http://www.nebel.tv/?p=106', 0, 'post', '', 0);
