(127, 3, '2013-11-13 11:22:15', '2013-11-13 11:22:15', '<p dir="ltr"></p>\n<p dir="ltr">So here we are :) Outlined below are the key milestones for the Nebel.TV project as we see them from the perspective of November, 2013.</p>\n\n<h2 dir="ltr">Website goes live! - November, 2013 (The Big-bang)</h2>\n<p dir="ltr">The readiness of the website, incorporating our new updated product graphical implementation, will commemorate the start of our active PR and communication campaign for the product, its development strategy and backing team. We will initially release three website sections:</p>\n<p dir="ltr">- Home page with an animated explanation of the Nebel.TV key features and concepts</p>\n<p dir="ltr">- About  - A description of the team - Who and what we are</p>\n<p dir="ltr">- Plan - the Nebel.TV’s team plan in regard to product development</p>\n<p dir="ltr">- BLOG - The team’s blog</p>\n<p dir="ltr">The website will be the primary promotion target for our initial marketing campaign to be rendered in major social networks as well as targeted media resources.</p>\n\n<h2 dir="ltr">Teaser App released - December, 2013 (Idea inflation)</h2>\n<p dir="ltr">The teaser application will mimic the idea of “movie trailers” which prefaces the release of every blockbuster to the cinema. It not only gives an idea about the product’s look-and-feel but also demonstrates the functionality of the future product and its value to the user. It is also a tool to demonstrate the team’s capabilities in developing a robust, easy-to-use and attractive mobile application. Although it will be greatly limited in the peer-2-peer streaming, media sharing and content playback features which are the objectives of the post-crowdfunding development stage.</p>\n\n<h2 dir="ltr">Crowdfunding Campaign start/finish - May, 2014 (Day-K)</h2>\n<p dir="ltr">Although the crowdfunding campaign itself will last for approx. 30 days, we expect this to be the pinnacle of the PR &amp; Communication campaign initiated in November, 2013. The aim of the  crowdfunding campaign will be to raise the evaluated amount of funds required for the development of the Nebel.TV application, including the PR&amp;Marketing campaign, project administration and overheads, initial network seeding as well as premiums for team members who shared in the risks of an unsuccessful crowd-sourcing campaign.</p>\n\n<h2 dir="ltr">Product release - December, 2014 (The Xmas gift)</h2>\n<p dir="ltr">Current milestones are tailored towards a Nebel.TV client application release onto the market with the following set of features as minimum: tracker-less media playback and sharing, media exchange security and integrated peer-2-peer financial transaction system.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">So, all in all - quite a busy period for the foreseeable future!! And with a lot of work from team Nebel.Tv (and the occasional whip and confiscation of tea and biscuits ;)  we''ll be winging Nebel.TV to you all soon.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">Cheers ;)</p>', 'Milestones to Nebel.TV', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'milestones-to-nebel-tv', '', '', '2013-11-13 11:22:15', '2013-11-13 11:22:15', '', 0, 'http://www.nebel.tv/?p=127', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(129, 3, '2013-11-13 11:41:04', '2013-11-13 11:41:04', '<p dir="ltr">WHY?</p>\n<p dir="ltr">Over recent years the technology for Television sets has been increasing at a drastic rate – from the changeover to digital broadcast compliancy as opposed to the old analogue, higher definition sets, 3D compatibility for your home (who would have thought), even to internet ready (Smart) TVs.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">However the attempt of leading TV manufacturers to equip their TV sets with computer-like features such as web browsers and apps, currently struggle due to the lack of appropriate user controls, as well as ridiculously feeble CPUs leaving them remarkably mismatched to the outstanding capabilities of modern FullHD or UHD TV sets. Yet with this whole new world of cutting edge visual technology the content sources of the TV set remains basically unchanged.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">Nebel.TV is a inspirational new free project aimed at revitalizing the World’s most common entertainment platform by creatively adapting existing technology and blending it social networking allowing for the evolution of how we use and enjoy our media in today’s mobile Social Generation.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">Nebel.TV is here to address all of the TV-platform’s shortcomings, delivering a superior content quality by means of streamlining advanced peer-2-peer media sharing technologies alongside a user-interface utilizing social network ideology &lt;link to blog article Social Generation&gt; to be able share your media with those in your network easily, privately and securely.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">For greater access Nebel.TV will be downloadable for free from Google Play directly to your tablet or phone giving you the freedom to enjoy access to your media whenever or wherever you wish, as well as being available in the neat convenient form of a HDMI dongle device (although this will not be needed to run the software on phones or tablets) for connection to your existing TV or home media library.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">That’s right! The Nebel.TV platform will be downloadable for free, and what’s more, once you have the software, it’s also free to use - no subscription fees!!!</p>\n<p dir="ltr">HOW?</p>\n<p dir="ltr">Nebel.TV aims to build its popularity from within internet communities, as we understand that the quickest way to gain public scrutiny/opinion is initially by opening up and promoting our project idea through these sources.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">Nebel.TV’s distribution and use will be free as we believe the way in which we enjoy our media should be our, the viewer/listener’s choice, not decided upon by a committee.</p>\n<p dir="ltr"> Currently we have used PayPal donation platform to start collecting funds. Later we will initiate our crowdfunding campaign in early May 2014. Using the crowdfunding platform allows YOU, the end user, to be a part of our dream, that being the evolution of how media should be enjoyed. Your donations will allow you to become part of the evolution, while we do the hard work using your money. We will have an in-depth blog &lt;blog link&gt; where you can actively follow our development progress, marketing campaigns as well as leave your comments and feedback on what you see.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">We are currently working on a project demo to be exhibited to the sourcing crowd where we hope to secure the funds for our projected &lt;milestone link&gt; final product release in Q4 2014.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">WHO?</p>\n<p dir="ltr">Nebel.TV is a project started early in 2013 by a group of 5 technology professionals each possessing over 15 years of development experience with different types of the software: traditional client-server, web, and mobile. Later the team has been expanded by 10+ more people spreading the team knowledge in other areas such as PR&amp;marketing, media and entertainment platforms and law.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">In August 2013, Nebel.TV has successfuly secured Seed 0 investment, from a reputable IT venture enterpreneur &lt;insert link&gt; and continued persuing it goal, to increase project awareness and get it to one of the crowd funding platforms.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">For the rogues gallery of Team Nebel.TV please visit &lt;insert link&gt;</p>\n<p dir="ltr">FEATURES</p>\n<p dir="ltr">1. Media Sharing – Sharing your media has now never been easier. Instant access to the media files of your friends. Keep full control over access to your own material, share only with those within your social circle.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">2. Enjoy both Live and Recorded content - Pause live broadcasts and continue watching whenever you choose, wherever you choose. Access the recorded content of your social network. Never miss anything again!</p>\n<p dir="ltr">3. Cutting edge technology for free - That’s right, pay absolutely nothing, zero, zilch, for the software download for your applicable device from the online store. Find out how we do this by visiting &lt;link to article&gt;</p>\n<p dir="ltr">4. Smart playback -  Instant media playback for audio or video (no waiting for your download) with automatic video down-scaling on display or network restricted devices. Flattened peer-2-peer media files exchange architecture: no central tracking or storage servers required.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">5. Smoothly integrated payment system: Pay and get paid for your own online content - No credit cards required. Live in a country not supported by Paypal? Not a problem...the integrated Bitcoin system gives you the best confidentiality possible. Tired of being flooded with advertising...now GET paid to view ads and spent the credit on your new content!</p>\n<p dir="ltr">6. Support your favorite artists without third party intervention - Directly reward the artist themselves for their creativity, not the recording label, hosting sites etc. Heard or seen something that you enjoyed? Want to help get this artist recognized? Pledge your support to their future projects.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">7. An Artist yourself? A budding independent filmmaker or creative musician? Promote your content and receive 100% royalties for your work by reaching out to a global audience.</p>\n<p dir="ltr">Remember, we want to share our dream with you, your donations will allow us all to be part of an evolved Social Generation!!!</p>', 'NEBEL.TV – At a Glance - Static Page t', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'nebel-tv-at-a-glance-static-page-t', '', '', '2013-11-13 11:41:04', '2013-11-13 11:41:04', '', 0, 'http://www.nebel.tv/?p=129', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(132, 3, '2013-11-13 12:36:21', '2013-11-13 12:36:21', 'Nebel.TV is a revolutionary new project aimed at revitalizing the World’s most common entertainment platform – television.\n\n<b>WHY </b>\n\nIn the flourishing modern era of the Internet, where advances in technology are changing every day, television still remains one of the most technologically stable platforms.\n\nThe attempt of leading TV manufacturers to equip their TV sets with computer-like features such as web browsers and apps, currently struggle due to the  lack of appropriate user controls, as well as ridiculously feeble CPUs leaving them remarkably mismatched to the outstanding capabilities of modern FullHD or UHD TV sets. Contrastingly, Google Chromecast and AppleTV lack access to appropriate high quality content, being limited to their contracts with the intellectual copyright owner’s companies and their distribution strategies.\n\nNebel.TV is here to address all of the TV shortcomings by delivering a superior content quality by streamlining advanced peer-2-peer media content exchange technologies featured with social networks and available in the neat convenient form of HDMI dongle devices or downloadable from Google PlayMarket directly to your Android tablet or phone.\n\n<b>HOW </b>We aim to popularize the Nebel.TV idea among Internet communities as we understand that the quickest way to reach public scrutiny to such projects is to initially promote the project idea within the Internet community. We will then create our crowd-sourcing campaign in early March, 2014. Currently, we are preparing a project demo to be exhibited to the sourcing crowd and hope to secure funds to make the product available in the last quarter of 2014.\n\n<b>WHO </b>Nebel.TV is a project started in 2013 by a group of technology geeks each possessing over 15 years of development experience with different types of the software: traditional client-server, web, and mobile.\n\nPlease write to <a href="mailto:contribute@nebel.tv">contribute@nebel.tv</a>  if you’d like to contribute to the project as a developer, tester, user experience guru or training material designer.\n\n<b>Features</b>\n\nNebel.TV will be available in two main formats:\n<ul>\n	<li>Android based smartphones and tablets</li>\n	<li>HDMI dongle or set-top-box HDMI connected device</li>\n</ul>\nMain Nebel.TV features:\n<ul>\n	<li>Flattened peer-2-peer media files exchange architecture: no central tracking or storage servers</li>\n	<li>Instant media playback (no waiting for your download) with low-res or screenshot previews</li>\n	<li>Integrated social network features: exchange your media with public, group or selected individuals</li>\n	<li>Alternating user profiles and strong user confidentiality protection</li>\n	<li>Integrated meta information sources: no need to upload media files meta information</li>\n	<li>Advanced media content profiling: integrated parental control and media filtering</li>\n	<li>Smartphone based remote control: no additional remotes to be lost</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Nebel.TV - Home - Edited', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'nebel-tv-home-edited', '', '', '2013-11-13 12:36:21', '2013-11-13 12:36:21', '', 0, 'http://www.nebel.tv/?p=132', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(165, 2, '2013-11-17 18:13:06', '2013-11-17 18:13:06', 'Recently, after speaking to many people and pitching the idea of Nebel.TV - I used to call it “The Next Generation Media Sharing Platform”. Well, that sounds bold at first glance, so I think it needs to be explained a little as to why I think so?...\n\nFirst lets put aside the “media sharing” part of that expression. Believe me, we will discuss that over the course of the next 6-8 months and there will be plenty of content related to this phrase. So for now, lets focus on why Nebel.TV is “Next Generation”.\n\nArguably, if we take a long look at the <a title="Features" href="http://www.nebel.tv/?page_id=23">features list of the Nebel.TV product</a> 	<link /> you will not find that many entries which are completely new. Even though the combination and integration of the features are new indeed, and that is a novelty in itself, but that hardly justifies Nebel.TV being labelled a Next Generation platform.\n\nThe first time I came closer to an answer, was during my search for the competitive advantages of Facebook, which allowed Mark to overtake the largely forgotten social network: “MySpace”. During FB’s infancy (July, 2006) MySpace was <a title="MySpace Charts in 2006" href="http://mashable.com/2006/07/11/myspace-americas-number-one/">topping the charts</a> of the US’ most ranked sites. So how could it happened that FB, which currently accounts for <a title="FB stats" href="http://news.yahoo.com/number-active-users-facebook-over-230449748.html">over 1B users/month</a> had overshadowed MySpace which in 2011 had been <a href="http://money.cnn.com/2011/06/29/technology/myspace_layoffs/index.htm?hpt=te_bn2">shaken off for a miserable $35M</a>?\n\nWell the answer I gave was 57 pages long (as it was supposed to look like a serious piece of academic work!) but fundamentally it can be boiled down to the following core statement: “The FB corporate culture and work process closely aligned with the product they aimed to deliver”. They succeeded to create a social network service by embracing and engaging FB’s employees and involved them in the use of their own product. (<small><em>Actually, I believe that the real threshold for this astonishingly popular network was Mark’s diffidence: he wasn''t able to ask if the girl he liked was in a relationship or not…</em></small> :)\n\nTo the extent of our organization (stay tuned! :) ) Nebel.TV is no different to FB. We’re a group of individuals who like media, sharing and online entertainment. We all share the vision of internet freedom, internet users equality and rights to access whatever information you need wherever and whenever you need it - John Perry Barlow’s 1996 paper “<a title="The Declaration of Cyberspace Independence" href="https://projects.eff.org/~barlow/Declaration-Final.html" target="_blank">The Declaration of the Independence of Cyberspace</a>” is a fantastic reference point ;). But as an extension to this, we would also like to build our social product using social funds (crowdfunding) and actively embrace social opinions, your opinions, into the shaping of the product and thereby influencing its development strategy. Meaning, at the end of the day, we deliver this product back to the society from where it grew and to where it belongs...\n\nI sincerely hope you can contribute to this goal. Just let us <a title="Mail US" href="mailto:contribute@nebel.tv" target="_blank">hear from you</a> and get involved, become a part of “The Next Generation Media Sharing Platform”!', 'Why do I call Nebel.TV The Next Generation Media Sharing Platform?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '165', '', '', '2013-11-17 18:13:06', '2013-11-17 18:13:06', '', 0, 'http://www.nebel.tv/?p=165', 0, 'post', '', 4),
(169, 4, '2013-11-18 21:39:41', '2013-11-18 21:39:41', 'The other day I came across quite an interesting article which posed the interesting question "http://www.nebel.tv/?p=165".\r\n\r\nI decided to also share my point of view  on this.\r\n\r\nBecause the statement is true, Nebel.TV really is the next necessary step in media technology.\r\n<strong>Why?</strong>\r\nBeing a guy who spends a lot of time in social networks I''m constantly confronted with various restrictions as to which one provides access to one or another network. For example, I am a big sports fan but many foreign TV channels are not broadcast in my country. I hear you say "Use the internet to find them" and that is so, that''s just what I do - but, on the other hand I have a lot of friends who also want to see this particular content but don''t know where to find it. As a result they come to me with the questions, "What are the results?" "Who won?" and most importantly "Where can I watch it?" Usually I just tell them the results and explain that I saw everything online. If I happen to have the media files, I load everything onto some file sharing site.\r\n\r\nWhat<strong><em> </em></strong>if we were to give you the opportunity to have a network, that combines all the media sources  you need? What if you have a TV, your video content, video blog or live journal all in one place? To use how and when you please! To share as well as control exactly with whom you share it whilst keeping your copyright - Share your video over the whole network or only distribute it between certain groups of friends! Never suffer from incompatibility, your content will be adapted to the capabilities of your devices without loss of quality!\r\n\r\nMost importantly... all this will be simple and easy for everyone to do ;)\r\n\r\n\\ Iaroslav Pavelskiy', 'Answering the question "Why do I call Nebel.TV The Next Generation Media Sharing Platform?"', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'why-do-i-call-nebel-tv-the-next-generation-media-sharing-platform', '', '', '2013-12-10 16:24:20', '2013-12-10 16:24:20', '', 0, 'http://www.nebel.tv/?p=169', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(174, 3, '2013-11-20 14:23:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Although the technology and idea of streaming full length Movies and TV episodes is relatively new, most people who have an internet connection are aware of this phenomenon. Obviously, if you’ve been following our <a title="Nebel Blog" href="http://www.nebel.tv/?page_id=26">blog </a>you’ll already know that Nebel.TV is trying to reinvigorate and expand upon the already available crop of streaming providers.\n\nWhether it’s called Streaming, Video on Demand (VOD), AVOD or even Catch-Up-TV they are all ways of being able to watch or indeed listen to your chosen form of entertainment. Obviously, with such a large variety of providers that exist today, it wouldn’t be feasible to go through each and every one individually, so I’m going to have a quick look at a couple of generic problems faced by our current competitors.\n\n<b>Price and Media Selection</b>\n\nHere we have one of the defining aspects of what platform we, as entertainment lovers, choose - granted there are just as many price ranges as providers but let’s look at this a little closer. At the budget end we have providers such as “Netflix” which weighs in at around $7-8/month – now this in itself isn’t bad and on the whole they do offer a relatively good and stable streaming package, <i>however </i>when it comes to budget package<i> </i>providers usually their selection of movies/TV shows are quite restricted, and more often than not their “new” additions are not really new in regards to being recent. Obviously this has something to do with licensing issues and their need to keep subscription rates down (of which they do a good job) but when it comes to wanting to watch something new and current, these providers can leave the viewer frustrated, especially when they don’t update their viewing selection for quite some time.\n\nAt the other end of the market we have the premium streaming packages from the likes of Sky in the UK and many others around the world that pump their on-demand content into your home directly to your digital TV. One of the drawbacks with these though is that you usually require to have a subscription to the specific channel that the program/film was originally aired on, also the vast majority of these major TV providers do not have all of their broadcast TV  available on-demand – and even that which is, isn’t usually available until the following day at the earliest.\n\nWhen it comes to sports fans, prices have a tendency to soar – you can pay upwards of $20/month just to access ONE channel for ONE kind of sport! Now you can only imagine the price you’d have to pay if you wanted to follow your favorite teams over numerous sports!\n\nEven though some of the premium subscription providers do offer quite a large selection of movies/TV episodes to watch, put simply your choice is still going to be based upon what content they as the provider have in their library which is of course based upon their server – so no matter what, your choice is still relatively restricted to what they allow you to have access to.\n\nSo where does Nebel.TV fit into all of this?\n\nThese premium providers are trying to improve their services, pumping lots of money into their R&amp;D departments (for better or worse) as they have realized that the future of TV is indeed by way of AVOD. So the timing for Nebel.TV couldn’t be better – joining\n\n&nbsp;', 'Audio and Video on Demand (AVOD) - Is it really as "Flexible" as we think? - NOT FINISHED - PLEASE DONT PUBLISH', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-11-20 14:23:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.nebel.tv/?p=174', 0, 'post', '', 0),
